3. Genre Analysis (Distribution of songs across different genres)¶

In [12]:
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
sns.countplot(x='playlist_genre', data=df)
plt.title('Distribution Of Songs Across Different Genres')
plt.xlabel('Genre')
plt.ylabel('Count')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.show()

4. Artist Analysis¶

In [13]:
# Analysing the popularity of different artists
artist_popularity = df.groupby('track_artist')['track_popularity'].mean().sort_values(ascending=False)

# Plotting the top N popular artist
top_n = 10
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
sns.barplot(x=artist_popularity.head(top_n).index, y=artist_popularity.head(top_n).values)
plt.title(f'Top {top_n} Popular Artists')
plt.xlabel('Artist')
plt.ylabel('Average Popularity')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.show()

5. Time-Based Analysis¶

In [15]:
# Converting 'track_album_release_date' to datetime
df['track_album_release_date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['track_album_release_date'])

# Analyzing trends in song releases over time
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 6))
sns.lineplot(x='track_album_release_date', y='track_popularity', data=df)
plt.title('Trends in Song Releases Over Time')
plt.xlabel('Release Date')
plt.ylabel('Popularity')
plt.show()

6. Playlist Analysis¶

6.1 Playlist Popularity¶

In [17]:
# Analyzing the popularity of playlists based on the aggregated popularity of their constituent tracks
playlist_popularity = df.groupby('playlist_name')['track_popularity'].mean().sort_values(ascending=False)

# Plotting the top N popular playlists
top_n = 10
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 6))
sns.barplot(x=playlist_popularity.head(top_n).index, y=playlist_popularity.head(top_n).values)
plt.title(f'Top {top_n} Popular Playlists')
plt.xlabel('Playlist')
plt.ylabel('Average Popularity')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.show()

6.2 Playlist Composition¶

In [18]:
# Explore the characteristics of playlists in terms of danceability, energy, etc.
playlist_characteristics = df.groupby('playlist_name').agg({
    'danceability': 'mean',
    'energy': 'mean',
    'loudness': 'mean',
    'speechiness': 'mean',
    'acousticness': 'mean',
    'instrumentalness': 'mean',
    'liveness': 'mean',
    'valence': 'mean',
    'tempo': 'mean'
})

# Plotting the characteristics of playlists
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
sns.heatmap(playlist_characteristics, cmap='coolwarm', annot=True)
plt.title('Playlist Characteristics')
plt.show()
